Biography

2024: Ohio Valley Conference All-Tournament Team selection…Played in all 54 games and made 49 starts…One of just two players who played in every game…Started 37 games at shortstop and 12 at second base…Hit .275 with 33 hits, 29 runs, four doubles, nine RBI, 10 walks and five stolen bases…In conference play, she hit .304 in 24 starts…Registered a season-high three hits and scored two runs vs. Tennessee State (3/23)…Had a total of six multiple-hit games…Went 4-for-6 with two runs scored and three RBI in two games against Eastern Illinois (5/10, 5/11) at the OVC Tournament…Hit .556 with three runs, a double and three RBI during Southeast Missouri’s OVC Tournament title run...Singled and scored a run against Arkansas (5/17) at the NCAA Regional.

2023: Garnered Second-Team All-OVC honors at second base…Participated in 40 games and made 33 starts…Hit .320 with 15 runs, 32 hits, two doubles, five triples and 16 RBI…Led Southeast Missouri in triples and stolen bases (10)…Walked four times…Was the Redhawks third-leading hitter in conference play with a .444 clip…Boasted a .627 slugging percentage and .429 on-base percentage against league foes…Did not commit an error in 21 OVC games which included 19 starts…Was the OVC leader in triples and ranked third in the league in batting average in conference games…Finished with a season-high three hits at Saint Louis (2/19) and vs. Morehead State (4/7)…Went 3-for-4 with a run scored against the Eagles…Tied for second on the team with 10 multiple-hit games…Had a total of five hits in the Redhawks series sweep of UT Martin (4/29-4/30)…Scored two runs in three contests…Finished the season with seven extra base hits, including two doubles and five triples…Committed only three errors for a .975 fielding percentage.

2022: Started 39 games at second base as a freshman…Hit .221 with 25 hits, 12 runs scored, a pair of doubles and 13 RBI…Walked five times and added three stolen bases…Saw action in 50 total games…Had multiple-hits in five games and multiple-RBI in three contests…Made her college debut with a single and two runs scored vs. Alabama A&M (2/11)…Notched a season-high three hits when she went 3-for-4 with a season-best three RBI at Tennessee Tech (3/26)…Ended her rookie campaign on a five-game hitting streak…Hit safely and scored in seven of her starts…Started 22 of 24 OVC games.

Prep: Claimed All-Conference and All-District honors all four of her prep seasons at Eureka High School…Named to the All-Region and All-Metro teams as a junior and senior…Hit .551 and led the Wildcats with a .931 slugging percentage and eight doubles…Had two triples, two home runs, 13 RBI and a team-high eight stolen bases that year as well…Was part of back-to-back conference championship teams (2018, 2019)…Set her school’s stolen base record…Also a member of the basketball, track & field and cross country teams…Was teammates with fellow SEMO signee Tatum Gerwitz on the St. Louis Chaos summer team.

Personal: Born December 6, 2002…Majoring in Engineering Physics…Daughter of Kenny and Kelley Dennis.
